If a variant is a predicted null variant in a gene where LOF is a known mechanism of disease (PVS1) , adding PM5 (Novel missense change at an amino acid residue where a different pathogenic missense change has been seen before) would not make sense
If a variant is a predicted null variant in a gene where LOF is a known mechanism of disease (PVS1) , adding PM4 (Protein length changing variant) will result in the redundant tags.

If a variant is a predicted null variant in a gene where LOF is a known mechanism of disease (PVS1) , adding PS1 (Same amino acid change as an established pathogenic variant)  will result in the redundant tags
If a variant is a predicted null variant in a gene where LOF is a known mechanism of disease (PVS1), adding BP1 (Missense when only truncating cause disease) will be contradicting.
If a variant is a predicted null variant in a gene where LOF is a known mechanism of disease (PVS1), adding BP7 (Silent variant with non predicted splice impact) is contradicting
If a variant is a predicted null variant in a gene where LOF is a known mechanism of disease (PVS1), adding BP3 (In-frame indels in repeat w/out known function) is contradicting

If a variant is a predicted null variant in a gene where LOF is a known mechanism of disease (PVS1), adding PP2 (Missense in gene with low rate of benign missense variants) will be contradictory evidence.
Length changing (PM4) and missense (PS1) variant will be contradictory.

Length changing (PM4) and missense (BP7) variant will be contradictory.
